      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"3. STEPHEN WITHERAP looks close to another win after finishing third last time (18.18) at this track. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. One of the leading chances. 8. ELECTRIC BLUE is a well performed sprinter ideally suited at the shorter trips. Last start was sixth over 388m at Gosford in a Grade 4/5 (22.56). Has a good record here at this journey including four wins. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Bold showing expected. 1. LIZZIE LONG LEGS was among the minors three back at Nowra then missed the frame the last two, but drawn box 1 this time where she has two wins. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the rails draw. Expecting significant improvement this line-up. 6. ANJO PRINCE won as favourite last time and is sure to feature again.\",\"runners\":[3,8,1,6],\"exclusive\":false}",
